AGI - I<span>l Custos of the Sacred Convent of St. Francis in Assisi Fr. Marco Moroni, OFMConv, wanted to call for peace in the world, in particular in Ukraine and in the Holy Land, on the occasion of the message of greetings for Easter. In the historical and social context in which Christians are preparing to celebrate the most important feast of the year, the words with which Jesus Risen presents himself to the disciples showing the wounds, “Peace to you”, the same peace that Saint Francis, on the inspiration of Christ, wished all “seminando” forgiveness. Even today, eight hundred years after the impression of the stigmata of Christ in his flesh, Francis continues to be a model, an inspiration and a guide for every man and woman operators of peace.</span>
&nbsp;
"It is time that everyone – he emphasizes between Marco in the video message –, on one side or on the other, in every conflict that still bloodses the world, does the most honorable, courageous and bold gesture: stop. Because we are, thanks to the wounds of the Risen One, a single family, brothers and sisters."
