In an attempt to reassure the public about its treatment, the United States declared that it would not be jailed in the ADX prison of Florence (Colorado), nicknamed "Alcatraz delle Montagne Rocciose" >, and that it would receive the necessary clinical and psychological care. The Americans had also ventilated the possibility that he asked for the penalty in Australia. Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese recently denounced the United States' criminal action against Assange and the Australian Parliament approved a motion calling for an end to it.
